Document: JavaScriptBridge
Path: godot/classes/class_javascriptbridge.rst
Summary: Provides a way to call JavaScript functions from GDScript and vice-versa in web exports.

JavaScriptBridge

Inherits: Object < Object

This class provides a way to call JavaScript functions from GDScript and vice-versa when exporting to the web. It's a singleton, so you can access it directly using JavaScriptBridge.

Key Rule: You can only use JavaScriptBridge when exporting your project to HTML5. It will not work in the editor or in native exports.

Methods:
call(function: String, ...params) → Variant
Calls a JavaScript function with the given name and arguments. Returns the value returned by the JavaScript function.

eval(script: String) → Variant
Evaluates a JavaScript script. Returns the value returned by the script.

is_connected() → bool
Checks if the JavaScript bridge is connected. This is true if the page is loaded and the bridge is ready.

connect()
Connects the JavaScript bridge. This is usually called automatically when the page is loaded.

disconnect()
Disconnects the JavaScript bridge. This is usually called automatically when the page is unloaded.
