Document: JavaScriptBridge
Path: godot/classes/class_javascriptbridge.rst
Summary: Provides access to the browser's JavaScript context when exporting to the web.
The JavaScriptBridge singleton is implemented only in the Web export. It's used to access the browser's JavaScript context. This allows interaction with embedding pages or calling third-party JavaScript APIs. Note: This singleton can be disabled at build-time to improve security. By default, the JavaScriptBridge singleton is enabled. Official export templates also have the JavaScriptBridge singleton enabled. See Compiling for the Web in the documentation for more information.
---CHUNK---
Document: JavaScriptBridge
Path: godot/classes/class_javascriptbridge.rst
Summary: Information about the JavaScriptBridge singleton for web export.

The JavaScriptBridge singleton allows communication between Godot and JavaScript when exporting to the web.

Inherits: Object

Methods:
  call(method: StringName, ...args: Variant) → Variant
    Calls a JavaScript function with the given name and arguments. Returns the value returned by the JavaScript function.

  eval(script: String) → Variant
    Evaluates a JavaScript script. Returns the value returned by the script.

  is_connected() → bool
    Checks if the JavaScript bridge is connected. This is true when the Godot project is running in a web environment and the bridge has been initialized.

Example:
GDScript:
```gdscript
func _ready():
    if JavaScriptBridge.is_connected():
        var result = JavaScriptBridge.call("my_js_function", "hello", 123)
        print(result)
        var eval_result = JavaScriptBridge.eval("1 + 1")
        print(eval_result)
    else:
        print("JavaScript bridge not connected.")
```
---CHUNK---
Document: JavaScriptBridge
Path: godot/classes/class_javascriptbridge.rst
Summary: This section details the methods available in the JavaScriptBridge class for interacting with JavaScript in a web environment.

Method: create_callback(callable: Callable) → JavaScriptObject
Creates a reference to a Callable that can be used as a callback by JavaScript. The reference must be kept until the callback happens, or it won't be called at all. See JavaScriptObject for usage.
Note: The callback function must take exactly one Array argument, which is going to be the JavaScript arguments object converted to an array.

Method: create_object(object: String, ...) → Variant |vararg|
Creates a new JavaScript object using the "new" constructor. The "object" must a valid property of the JavaScript window. See JavaScriptObject for usage.

Method: download_buffer(buffer: PackedByteArray, name: String, mime: String = "application/octet-stream") → void
Prompts the user to download a file containing the specified "buffer". The file will have the given "name" and "mime" type.
Note: The browser may override the MIME type provided based on the file "name"'s extension.
Note: Browsers might block the download if download_buffer is not being called from a user interaction (e.g. button click).
Note: Browsers might ask the user for permission or block the download if multiple download requests are made in a quick succession.

Method: eval(code: String, use_global_execution_context: bool = false) → Variant
Execute the string "code" as JavaScript code within the browser window. This is a call to the actual global JavaScript function eval().
If "use_global_execution_context" is true, the code will be evaluated in the global execution context. Otherwise, it is evaluated in the execution context of a function within the engine's runtime environment.

Method: force_fs_sync() → void
Force synchronization of the persistent file system (when enabled).
Note: This is only useful for modules or extensions that can't use FileAccess to write files.

Method: get_interface(interface: String) → JavaScriptObject
Returns an interface to a JavaScript object that can be used by scripts. The "interface" must be a valid property of the JavaScript window. The callback must accept a single Array argument, which will contain the JavaScript arguments. See JavaScriptObject for usage.

Method: is_js_buffer(javascript_object: JavaScriptObject) → bool
Returns true if the given "javascript_object" is of type ArrayBuffer, DataView, or one of the many typed array objects.

Method: js_buffer_to_packed_byte_array(javascript_buffer: JavaScriptObject) → PackedByteArray
Returns a copy of "javascript_buffer"'s contents as a PackedByteArray. See also is_js_buffer.

Method: pwa_needs_update() → bool |const|
Returns true if a new version of the progressive web app is waiting to be activated.
Note: Only relevant when exported as a Progressive Web App.

Method: pwa_update() → Error
Performs the live update of the progressive web app. Forcing the new version to be installed and the page to be reloaded.
Note: Your application will be reloaded in all browser tabs.
Note: Only relevant when exported as a Progressive Web App and pwa_needs_update returns true.